{"id": "EUVD-2025-29578", "enisaUuid": "5bd1710d-65dc-340f-aec8-ca5d4c680888", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nefi: stmm: Fix incorrect buffer allocation method\n\nThe communication buffer allocated by setup_mm_hdr() is later on passed\nto tee_shm_register_kernel_buf(). The latter expects those buffers to be\ncontiguous pages, but setup_mm_hdr() just uses kmalloc(). That can cause\nvarious corruptions or BUGs, specifically since commit 9aec2fb0fd5e\n(\"slab: allocate frozen pages\"), though it was broken before as well.\n\nFix this by using alloc_pages_exact() instead of kmalloc().", "datePublished": "2025-09-16T15:32:36", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-02T00:31:09", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/77ff27ff0e4529a003c8a1c2492c111968c378d3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/630c0e6064daf84f17aad1a7d9ca76b562e3fe47", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c5e81e672699e0c5557b2b755cc8f7a69aa92bff", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39836"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39836"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "38de4492-c9a5-3b1a-9600-60cb1697a10d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.45"}, {"id": "4f7d2211-bcdc-39c3-9bfb-9bfbd9606a6d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.8"}, {"id": "54a13b2d-0855-30f6-849d-95a336094d07", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c44b6be62e8dd4ee0a308c36a70620613e6fc55f <630c0e6064daf84f17aad1a7d9ca76b562e3fe47"}, {"id": "81307a18-429a-3884-8322-32e14e1ce380", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c44b6be62e8dd4ee0a308c36a70620613e6fc55f <77ff27ff0e4529a003c8a1c2492c111968c378d3"}, {"id": "a0409ee6-9a24-30c1-b7c3-1adcab43b3f7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17-rc4"}, {"id": "aa475b30-5cf5-3ac3-a0e4-4e22d654406e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.5"}, {"id": "cc368afe-a031-3662-8ff5-787e962fade1", "product": {"nam